Description: Provides data from a systematic literature review assessing open
    data practices in biologging research. The review queried Web of Science
    Core Collection (2023-08-21) for biologging-related publications across
    twelve ecological and biological subject categories, yielding 4,799 papers.
    Each paper was scored by at least two reviewers on manuscript type, whether
    novel biologging data were presented, deployment context (wild, captive, or
    domesticated), sensor categories used (location, intrinsic, environment),
    focal species taxonomy, and whether a data availability statement addressed
    the biologging data. Two datasets are included -  'biologging', one row per
    reviewed paper, and 'taxa', taxonomic records for studies involving multiple
    species.
